sjsu continues to monitor developments around the emergence of mpox. although case numbers are small relative to the general population and covid-19 cases, it is a health concern for anyone exposed. exposure happens primarily through skin-to-skin contact with someone who is symptomatic. visit the medical services page to learn more about the symptoms of mpox and precautions you can take. august 16, 2022 - monkeypox advisory and information email: healthadvisories@sjsu.edu sign up for alert sjsu 